  "text": "Indian Remote Sensing Satellite data (IRS P6 LISS III and LISS IV) procured from the National Remote Sensing Centre was used to delineate the rainforest fragments in the Valparai plateau. LISS III images have a spatial resolution of 23.8 m, while for those of LISS IV it is 5.8 m. The LISS III data were geometrically corrected with respect to Enhanced Thematic Mapper (ETM+) satellite data based on 1 st order polynomial regression between ground control points (RMSE<0.5 pixel) -tion equations, and registered to the UTM projection. Further to this, geometric correction of the LISS IV data was carried out with respect to LISS III data. The other data pre-processing techniques applied have been detailed elsewhere [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The rainforest fragments were delineated at a scale of 1: 10,000. Field surveys were conducted to They were found in three, all owned by private enterprises in the Puthuthottam Estate, the Korangumudi Estate and the Tata Estate (hereafter the fragments are named with the name of the estate).",
